Makes a climate-resilient solution that preferentially selects planning units that are more climate-resilient than others. The climate-resilience metric combines climate exposure and climate velocity. High climate-resilience metric pertains to areas with less climate exposure (lower temperature increase in the future) and slower climate velocity (climate refugia where species are more likely to be retained in the selected planning units under warming).
